folder: Pearl Street & Maiden Lane, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)
Pearl Street, west side, north from and including Maiden Lane and showing a general view northward, as seen from the Seaman's Bank for Savings, at No. 74 Wall Street. Also shown is Maiden Lane, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Pearl Street. The Second and Third Ave. Elevated is shown on Pearl Street. Prominent in the background, is No. 111 John Street at the N.W. corner of Pearl Street. (Pearl Street, is arbitrarily set to run north and south).
June 13, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from a different angle. October 1, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, showing a closer view of the upper floors of the smaller buildings. June 4, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.
